><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 3:28:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3793.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 1.52d, new information on armor resists:</span><hr size=1> NEW ARMOR TABLES <br>We have change the armor tables for the game. Previously, the armor tables worked in such a manner that it was advantageous for melee characters to specialize only in crushing/blunt/hammer weapons. Now, the armor tables are spread out more evenly, giving all armor advantages and disadvantages against every weapon type. <br><br>In doing this change, we have also added armor types specifically for the Hibernian Scale and Reinforced armors. No longer do they mimic chain and studded armor tables as they used to - now they have their own unique characteristics. <br><br>Also, in RvR only, we have doubled the amount that a particular armor's bonus reduces damage against a weapon type that it is protected against. This will reduce the overall damage that players take when hit by a weapon or bolt spell that their armor protects against. <br><br>Plate Chain Scale Reinf Stud Leath Cloth <br>T High Vuln Low Low High High Neut <br>C Vuln Low High Vuln Vuln Low Neut <br>S Low High Vuln High Low Vuln Neut <br><br>Vuln = vulnerable <br>High = high resist, etc. <br>T = Thrust, C = Crush, S = Slash <br><br><br>Here's the user friendly version and how it applies to us:<br><br><br>Thrust bonuses/penalties:<br>-- Plate<br>++ Chain<br>- Scale<br>- Reinforced <br>-- Studded<br>-- Leather<br>-+ Cloth<br>(Piercing got hosed a bit)<br><br>Slash bonuses/penalties:<br>- Plate<br>-- Chain<br>++ Scale<br>-- Reinforced<br>- Studded<br>++ Leather<br>-+ Cloth<br>(Hibbie scale wearers [heroes/wardens/druids/champs] can get smacked around now by Infiltrators and Shadowblades. Nightshades do not have any scale targets)<br><br>Crush bonuses/penalties:<br>++ Plate<br>- Chain<br>-- Scale<br>++ Reinforced<br>++ Studded<br>- Leather<br>-+ Cloth<br>(Just in case we're facing anyone with a hammer)<br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A> at: 7/24/02 3:41:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 3:45:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3793.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1.52d, new information on armor resists:</span><hr size=1> From a Nightshade piercing perspective, we got hosed, especially since the bonuses (not penalties) of armor is doubled for RvR. Eeeeeooooouuuuuccccchhhhh!!!!!!<br><br>Slashing is even worse. Combined with the hardships of being a low stat/poor style Bladeshade, they don't have an additional target like the other Assassins do. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubalorgafdan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balor Gafdan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 3:47:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3793.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.camelotherald.com/guilds/nightshade.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1.52d, new information on armor resists:</span><hr size=1> /cries<br>Oh piercing, how i have stuck with you for so long.. and now this.. <br>/cries<br><br><br>Slash bonuses/penalties:<br>- Plate