Archers who were previously at a 15% resist to piercing damage are now at a 30% resist, PLUS any thrust resists from magic, PLUS the inherant protection of 100% quality epic armor and the 35% bonus.<br><br>You can bet every archer in the game will respec now to slash, thanks to the 30% vulnerablity that leather has to it.<br><br>So, no more archers for Nightshades.  Fine.  What is vulnerable to Piercing?  Chain.<br><br>Every chain user in the game now has a reason to spec to slash, because it's what the Hib tanks are vulnerable to (as well as leather users).  Chain wearers also belong to classes and races with high hitpoints and strength ANYWAY.<br><br>And heaven help me if I don't want respec to slashing (for a myriad of reasons:  Piercing has better styles, I prefer the look and delay of piercing weapons, roleplay, etc), because you know other assassins WILL making my low hit point, low strength Nightshade even MORE at a loss when compared to the other assassin classes, who start with a higher base strength and con.<br><br>That leaves me with ... mages.  Wow.  How fun.  One class that makes an ideal target now, instead of the former choices I had of <br><br>-Mages<br>-Archers with some small difficulty<br>-Other assassins with some small difficulty<br>-Chain wearers with more difficulty (50/50 chance)<br><br>I don't see how this is a good thing.  I *sincerely* hope it works out better in testing than it does on paper.  I won't be home for another 2 hours, but right now I don't see much to look forward to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelaa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elaa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/02 3:58:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3793.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top